snippet.title: 'Pink beauty'  Amber Heard hikes after petitions to fire her from Aquaman 2
snippet.description:
Amber heard has been hitting the canyons of Los Angeles for hikes in recent months, as part of her exercise routine amid the COVID-19 pandemic.

And on Monday Amber Heard was back at it again, soaking up the autumn air with a friend and her beloved dog Birdie by her side.

The afternoon excursion comes around the same time she took to her Instagram Story to promote her leading lady role in the dark fantasy miniseries, The Stand, which is based on the 1978 novel of the same name by Stephen King.

The actress, 34, worked up a sweat in skin-tight black leggings and a pink t-shirt that she bunched-up in the front to give a hint of her toned midriff.

She also wore a black sneakers and had a red bandana tied around her neck as she carried a black backpack over her shoulders.

The Texas native rounded out the sporty ensemble by pulling her long blonde tresses back into a ponytail as she took turns walking her dog with her gal pal.      


Heard stars as Nadine Cross in The Stand TV series, which debuts on CBS All Access on December 17.


With the world decimated by plague and embroiled in an elemental struggle between good and evil, the story is focused on the fate of mankind and how it rests on the frail shoulders of the 108-year-old Mother Abagail and a handful of survivors.   

It also stars James Marsden, Greg Kinnear, Odessa Young, Henry Zaga, Whoopi Goldberg, Alexander Skarsgård, Jovan Adepo and Ezra Miller, among others
